Job Description
Organizational Context
Under the guidance of the UNDP Provincial Representative, the Provincial Coordination Officer will be responsible to support the overall coordination of the UNDP Programme in Balochistan, and provide technical support to the Government of Balochistan on the UNDP’s programme and operations related matters.
While Balochistan has some important natural resources such as minerals, horticulture, livestock and fisheries, progress has been halted due to the many constraints which bind the Province including security concerns, endemic poverty, water constraints, low population density weak private sector and institutions and low skilled manpower. Over 52% off all households are living under the poverty line and of these three quarters of all of these households live in rural areas. The level of school participation in Balochistan is significantly less than in other areas, and is particularly low for girls: only 20% of women ever attend school and only 13% have ever completed primary level education or ahead. Key growth priorities of inclusive, sustainable growth and employment creation must be coupled with increased community participation and organization in the development of the Province to help combat the rise of insurgency.
UNDP has currently four cross-sector initiatives in the Province and in the areas of Governance, Environment, Conflict Prevention and Recovery and Inclusive Growth.
The UNDP Provincial Coordination Officer will support the UNDP Provincial Representative on all aspects of the CO programme based in the province of Balcohistan, including strategic planning, monitoring the implementation of ongoing projects and providing creative responses to emerging challenges and opportunities. The Provincial Coordination Officer will act as a liaison with the Government of Balochistan and will work in close coordination with UNDP project teams in Balochistan, UNDP Country Office staff, other UN Agency staff, Government officials, technical advisors and experts, donors and civil society to successfully support the implementation the UNDP programme in Balochistan. Functions / Key Results Expected Summary of Key Functions: ·
Liaison with Government of Balochistan on all issues related to UNDP programme and operations
·
Support coordination of UNDP project teams in Balochistan
·
Support development, implementation and monitoring of the provincial programme strategy
·
Support partnership initiatives to promote UNDP mandate in Balochistan
1.
Liaison with Government of Balochistan on all issues related to UNDP programme and operations
·
Support for development needs assessments in Balochistan
·
Support for identification of areas of capacity development for the Government of Balochistan
·
Ensure that the Government of Balochistan is well informed of UNDP’s priorities and activities
·
Maintain close liaison with the government counterparts to ensure UNDP programme coherence and alignment with the government priorities
·
Coordination of UNDP missions/visits to Balochistan
2.
Support coordination of the UNDP project teams in Balochistan
·
Support the design and formulation of UNDP Provincial programme, translating UNDP priorities into local interventions.
·
Coordination of programme implementation with the executing agencies.
·
Information sharing and identification of synergies between different UNDP projects in the Province. ·
Identification and organization of training opportunity for project staff.
3.
Support development, implementation and monitoring of the provincial programme strategy
·
Support effective application of RBM tools and monitoring achievement of results
·
Support the development of the provincial M&E strategy in coordination with the Country Office and relevant stakeholders.
·
Provide consolidated reports on UNDP activities in the province.
·
Carry out field visits to verify project results.
·
Aggregate reports are regularly prepared on activities, outputs and outcomes. ·
Support for the preparation of donor reports. 4.
Support partnership initiatives to promote UNDP mandate in Balochistan
·
Support for the implementation of the CO partnerships and resources mobilization strategies to achieve programme outcomes. ·
Creation and coordination of partnerships with the UN Agencies, IFI’s, government institutions, bi-lateral and multi-lateral donors, private sector, civil society etc.
·
Analysis and research of information on donors, preparation of substantive briefs on possible areas of cooperation, identification of opportunities for cost-sharing. IV. Impact of Results The key results have an impact on the overall success of the country programme and reaching UNDAF/ CPD goals, with a focus on Balochistan. In particular, the key results have an impact on the design, operation and programming of activities, creation of strategic partnerships as well as reaching resource mobilization targets. “Recommended/Alternate candidates resulting from the selection process will also be kept on our Roster for future similar positions for the timeframe of two years”.
